16 through training and mentorship, conducted extensive street outreach, and offered life skills
17 coaching and professional development programs; and
18 WHEREAS, Alisa has served as a beacon of hope in her community by using her personal
19 journey to inspire and uplift others, providing compassionate leadership and a faith-driven
20 approach that helps women embrace purposeful and fulfilling lives; and
21 WHEREAS, it is abundantly fitting and proper that the outstanding accomplishments of this
22 extraordinary servant leader be appropriately recognized.
23 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE that the members of this body
24 congratulate and commend Alisa Anderson for receiving the 2025 Yellow Rose Nikki T.
25 Randall Servant Leader Award and extend best wishes for her continued success.
26 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Secretary of the Senate is authorized and directed
27 to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to Alisa Anderson.
